cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the problem of hinged dissections of polygons, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of a circle-packing algorithm for quadrilateral mesh generation suggests a connection to mesh generation (cs.GR) and possibly also to computational topology (cs.MM). The algorithmic aspect of the problem and the time complexity analysis suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of a specific algorithm for the dissection suggests a connection to computer graphics (cs.SI).
